  .","Altered form of American French   Breaux   back to its original form."]},{"name":"Breau","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Ulysse, Alcide, Antoine, Aurore, Girard, Leonide, Mederic, Ovila, Raoul, Yves, Yvon.","American French: variant of   Breaux  , and an altered form of its French cognates   Braud   and   Brault  .","French (<b>Bréau</b>): variant of <b>Breuil</b> (see   Dubreuil  )."]},{"name":"Breaud","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Urbain, Nemour.","American French: variant of   Breaux  .","In some cases possibly also French (<b>Bréaud</b>): variant of   Beraud  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Egelina","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the girl's name   Evelyn  , or a combination of   Eve   with the suffix <i>-lina</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":34,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":69,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":100,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Egelina de Préaux was born in 1190, in Dartmouth, Devon, England, her father, Pierre Preaux, was 15 and her mother, F Preaux, was 15. She had at least 1 son with Phillip de Columbaris. She died in 1300, in Honiton, Devon, England, at the age of 110, and was buried in Honiton, Devon, England."},"et":{"1190–1300":"1190–1300","1140–1186":"1140–1186","1209–1262":"1209–1262","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1190":"1190","20 September 1262":"20. september 1262","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1262":"1262","1140":"1140","1290":"1290","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1300":"1300","1209":"1209","Nether Stowey, Somerset, England":"Nether Stowey, Somerset, England","Heathfield, Honiton, Devonshire, England":"Honiton, Devon, England","Dartmouth, Devonshire, England":"Dartmouth, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1190–1300":"1190–1300","1140–1186":"1140–1186","1209–1262":"1209–1262","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1190":"1190","20 September 1262":"20. syyskuuta 1262","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1262":"1262","1140":"1140","1290":"1290","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1213":"1213","1224":"1224","1300":"1300","1209":"1209","Nether Stowey, Somerset, England":"Nether Stowey, Somerset, England","Heathfield, Honiton, Devonshire, England":"Honiton, Devon, England","Dartmouth, Devonshire, England":"Dartmouth, Devon, England"},"fr":{"1190–1300":"1190–1300","1140–1186":"1140–1186","1209–1262":"1209–1262","1175–1213":"1175–1213","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","1190":"1190","20 September 1262":"20 septembre 1262","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1262":"1262","1140":"1140","1290":"1290","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1